body.description: Pack all your travel essentials with ease in this Kenneth Cole Reaction 'Renegade' Collection 20-inch lightweight, hardside, expandable 8-wheel spinner carry-on suitcase. This dependable carry-on suitcase is loaded with amazing features, including a spacious fully lined, tear-resistant interior, multiple interior zipper pockets and mesh pockets, a garment restraint panel to hold your clothes in place, and two elastic shoe pockets. This suitcase bag even expands an additional 2-inches for extra carrying capacity when needed. The exterior of this carry on suitcase features four molded corner guard reinforcements that provide maximum impact resistance, protecting your bag from excessive wear-and-tear. Self-repairing coil zippers designed for long-lasting use to glide effortlessly around the bag to keep your belongings safe and secure. The luggage boasts a lightweight construction to help you adhere to airline weight restrictions and avoid unwanted airport fees. Smooth, multi-directional 8-wheel spinners provide 360-degree rotation over any surface, allowing you to travel with ease. Features a sturdy, locking, retractable push-button telescopic trolley handle that extends 41 inches tall and is conductive to simple one-handed use. The 20" carry-on suitcase size was designed to meet most U.S. based and international airline carry-on size requirements and designed to fit into most airline overhead bin compartments. This Kenneth Cole Reaction 'Renegade' 20" carry-on suitcase is a modern, yet traditional carry on suitcase, perfect for travelers whom value both style and function. ★ Backed by a manufacturer’s 10-year limited guarantee against defects. ★ Overall Dimensions includes handles and wheels. ★ 20" Carry-on overall dimensions: 22” H x 14” w x 9” – 11” D. ★ 20" Packing Dimensions: 20” H x 13.5” w x 8.5” - 10.5" D. ★ 20" Weight: 7.35 lbs. ★

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bought Two and they are Amazing!
reviews.reviewText: I searched forever to find the right suitcase for my needs. The one thing I love about this Suitcase is the different pockets it has and that both sides close. One is with snaps and the other a zipper. Nice and secure!The only downside is that is that it doesn't come with a lock. But that didn't stop me from buying these. The wheels are amazing and glide across the airport floor. My luggage made it safe through the airports and flying.I was able to stuff an entire box full of bags for our business expo using the extension zipper. It was great!I will use again most definitely!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for me!
reviews.reviewText: Here’s the gist, I love them. Lots of space and the pockets make great use of the interior and allow for smarter packing. The big test was 10 days all across Europe and they held up great and I had more than enough room to go and to bring back souvenirs (I’m an over packer for sure!). I was impressed when we needed to walk about 2 miles on the the cobblestone streets and the wheels did great!Full story is that we purchased two of these before a coast to coast flight in the US. We were gone for 12 days and found that we had more than enough room. I then took the pink one for 4 more coast to coast flights and it is now pretty scratched on the outside and 1 or 2 shallow dents, but it doesn’t bother me much. It’s held up great otherwise! The green one is not nearly as scratched but hasn’t traveled as much. I would certainly buy these again. The only issue has been the scratched exterior so maybe get one of those bags that covers them for the flights?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great suitcase for it's first trip!
reviews.reviewText: We bought the 24inch suitcase for an upcoming international trip. We tried them out on a shorter trip to Hawaii last week. They are very lightweight, and easy to maneuver, the wheels seem to work great. When packed, my bag weighed 37 pounds, and I didn't have any trouble with the handle on top or on the side. It actually fit more items than I thought it would for its size. I'm optimistic about our next trip, will update if there are any problems, but so far it seems to be a good value!UPDATE: After 14 months, the handle broke on my suitcase, the screw that holds the top piece to the retractable bars fell out. The suitcase otherwise looks great, the black plastic on the underside near the wheels came loose earlier, but no other issues and the outside is not scuffed (Thanks Delta!). I emailed customer service due to the 10 year warranty and will update any resolution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars No set in locks
reviews.reviewText: Gave a 4 because it did not have the locks that are built in. I would have order the other one. I bought refurbished. Did not say it had a zipper that you supply lock. Luggage is nice. New for me to have hard case no out side pockets. An adjustment. Love that separate inside zips close. That flap has pockets. To keep organized. Wheels are easy rolling and turning. Super light weight. Handle adjust up and down easily. Stable. Wish it had the new built in locks. No going to trouble to send back. Adapt and overcome. Minor problem

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My second set—very durable!
reviews.reviewText: This is my second set of this particular set of luggage. I really wanted to have a set similar to the Bric’s with the cream and cognac leather, but just couldn’t stomach the expense after reading reviews…so I came back to my tried-and-true. I’m honestly hoping these last like my first ones (purchased January of 2016). My husband travels over seas for work every other month and we have had no issues with anything about them being destroyed by airline workers. The originals I have are white and black and my only complaint of those were the scuffs were so visible and small tears to interior lining that in no way made them unusable. I’m only buying a new set that is mine—he can have the OG’s😂. This time around I purchased the gold/champagne colored ones. They’re quite nice. My main goal is to be able to spot them at baggage claim. Hopefully I never have to come report anything different! Posting photos of the largest ones side by side—white is the one that has lasted more global travel than the average luggage sees!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect roller checked bag
reviews.reviewText: Love the size, compartments are extremely user-friendly and perfect for the things I already pack, having their own perfect spot; it did not get tripped up on the wheels, but moved very smoothly. Extremely lightweight, the dark teal/emerald color is beautiful and unique. The zippers quite smooth. One thing I would change is with how smooth the zipper is, adding a clipping or locking feature to make the zipper parts stay together. I haven’t had any accidents but, because it moves so easily have been tying them together before checking the bag. But I absolutely love it!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I got an amazing deal on the medium-size luggage during Prime Day before the pandemic so it sat in my closet for a while, but I've finally started using it over the last year. It has gone on 3 round trips with layovers (so 12 flights total and 6 rounds on the carousel) and a road trip. I've dragged it over curbs, sidewalks, gravel, and all sorts of hotel surfaces and hauled it into cabs and rental car trunks. It has some scratches, as expected, but no dents, and all wheels, zippers, and handles are still perfectly functional. I can't seem to pack light so I have used it fully expanded and packed to its maximum capacity for longer trips.I use packing cubes and also have heavy-duty luggage straps to lighten the load on the zippers and joints. I love that I can immediately recognize my luggage on the carousel with the gorgeous rose gold color and luggage straps. I also purchased a separate TSA lock since the luggage doesn't have one built in.Overall, I am extremely happy with the purchase and definitely think it was worth every penny.
This was the exact colour match to my one piece checked on luggage.
I love the quality of this Luggage!
